{% if style_context and style_context.pre_translation_analysis %}
{% set analysis = style_context.pre_translation_analysis %}
{% set profile = analysis.get("document_profile") or analysis %}
<PRE_TRANSLATION_CONTEXT>
{% if profile.get("document_type") %}
- document_type: {{ profile.get("document_type") }}
{% endif %}
{% if profile.get("domain") %}
- domain: {{ profile.get("domain") }}
{% endif %}
{% if profile.get("workflow") %}
- workflow: {{ profile.get("workflow") }}
{% endif %}
{% if profile.get("product_system") %}
- product/system: {{ profile.get("product_system") }}
{% endif %}
{% if profile.get("purpose") %}
- purpose: {{ profile.get("purpose") }}
{% endif %}
{% if profile.get("audience") %}
- audience: {{ profile.get("audience") }}
{% endif %}
{% if profile.get("content_structure") %}
- content_structure: {{ profile.get("content_structure") }}
{% endif %}
{% if profile.get("style") or profile.get("tone") %}
- source register observation: {{ profile.get("style", "") }}{% if profile.get("tone") %}; tone: {{ profile.get("tone") }}{% endif %}{{ "\n" }}
{% endif %}
- Use this as source-only document context, not as terminology.
- Apply the document domain, workflow, product/system context, audience, and observed register only when interpreting the current {{ source_label }}.
- Do not translate, copy, summarize, or output this context section.
- Do not make final term decisions from this section. Use Document Term Memory for terminology.
- Do not use this section to override Document Term Memory, explicit local context, Style Options, or Style Guide rules.
- Do not treat source register observations as user-requested output style. User style options and Style Guide rules decide the final target-language style.
- Do not add domain knowledge that is not supported by the source text, Document Term Memory, or this pre-translation context.

{% if analysis.get("domain_context") %}
DOMAIN / WORKFLOW CONTEXT:
{% for item in analysis.get("domain_context") %}
- {{ item }}
{% endfor %}

{% endif %}
{% if analysis.get("participants_and_roles") %}
PARTICIPANT / RELATIONSHIP CONTEXT:
{% for item in analysis.get("participants_and_roles") %}
- {{ item.get("source") }}{% if item.get("document_local_role") %}: {{ item.get("document_local_role") }}{% endif %}{% if item.get("relationship_or_dependency") %}; relationship/dependency: {{ item.get("relationship_or_dependency") }}{% endif %}{% if item.get("register_or_speech_relevance") %}; register cue: {{ item.get("register_or_speech_relevance") }}{% endif %}{% if item.get("why_it_matters") %}; why it matters: {{ item.get("why_it_matters") }}{% endif %}{{ "\n" }}
{% endfor %}
- Use this section to interpret participant roles, institutional dependencies, and dialogue/register cues.
- Do not turn this section into terminology rules. Do not translate or output these labels.
- For direct speech, combine this initial relationship context with local dialogue_hint and DOCUMENT_TRANSLATION_MEMORY Target register notes.

{% endif %}
{% if analysis.get("style_guidance") %}
SOURCE REGISTER OBSERVATIONS:
{% for item in analysis.get("style_guidance") %}
- {{ item }}
{% endfor %}
- These are observations about this document's register, not separate style rules. Apply them only when they do not conflict with Style Options or Style Guide Rules.

{% endif %}
</PRE_TRANSLATION_CONTEXT>
{% endif %}
